{
  "local_port": 47020,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the procedure to check your PF balance?",
  "response": "Checking your Employee Provident Fund (PF) balance is essential to keep track of your savings and ensure that your employer is contributing correctly. There are multiple ways to check your PF balance, primarily through the Employees' Provident Fund Organisation (EPFO) in India. Below are the detailed procedures for the most common methods:\n\n### **1. Online Through the EPF Member Portal**\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n- **Universal Account Number (UAN):** Ensure your UAN is activated and linked to your bank account and member ID.\n- **Password:** You must have set up your password for the EPF member portal.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Visit the EPFO Portal:**\n   - Go to the official EPFO member portal: [https://unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in/memberinterface/](https://unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in/memberinterface/)\n\n2. **Login:**\n   - Enter your **UAN** and **password**, then click on the **\"Sign In\"** button.\n\n3. **Navigate to the Dashboard:**\n   - Once logged in, you'll see an overview dashboard. Look for the **\"View\"** options.\n\n4. **Select \"View Passbook\":**\n   - Click on **\"View\"** and then select **\"Passbook\"** from the dropdown menu.\n\n5. **Verify Details:**\n   - Your PF balance will be displayed along with the contributions and withdrawals. You can also download or print your passbook for future reference.\n\n### **2. Using the UMANG App**\n\nThe UMANG (Unified Mobile Application for New-age Governance) app by the Government of India allows you to access various services, including checking your PF balance.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Download and Install the UMANG App:**\n   - Available on both [Google Play Store](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.umang.app&hl=en&gl=US) and [Apple App Store](https://apps.apple.com/in/app/umang-government-services/id1365979066).\n\n2. **Register/Login:**\n   - Open the app and register using your mobile number. Ensure your mobile number is linked to your UAN.\n\n3. **Access PF Services:**\n   - In the search bar, type **\"EPF\"** or navigate to the **\"Employment & Labour\"** section.\n\n4. **Select \"Provident Fund\":**\n   - Choose **\"Provident Fund\"** from the list of services.\n\n5. **View Your Passbook:**\n   - After authentication, your PF balance and passbook details will be displayed.\n\n### **3. Via SMS**\n\nFor those who prefer simple text messages, EPFO provides an SMS service to check PF balance.\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n- Your **UAN** should be registered with your mobile number.\n- UAN must be activated and linked with your Aadhaar number.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Compose SMS:**\n   - Type **\"EPFOHO UAN ENG\"** (Replace \"ENG\" with the first three letters of your preferred language, e.g., \"HIN\" for Hindi).\n\n2. **Send to 7738299899:**\n   - Open your SMS app and send the composed message to the number **7738299899**.\n\n3. **Receive Response:**\n   - You will receive an SMS containing your PF balance and related details.\n\n### **4. By Giving a Missed Call**\n\nA quick way to get your PF balance is by requesting an IVRS call.\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n- Your mobile number should be registered with your UAN.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Dial 011-22901406:**\n   - This is the EPFO office number.\n\n2. **Missed Call:**\n   - Simply dial this number and hang up before the call is connected.\n\n3. **Receive SMS:**\n   - You will receive an SMS with your PF balance and last deposit date within a few minutes.\n\n### **5. Through Employer or HR Department**\n\nIf you have difficulties accessing your PF balance through online methods, you can request the information from your company's HR or payroll department.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Contact HR:**\n   - Reach out to your Human Resources or Payroll department.\n\n2. **Request PF Statement:**\n   - Ask them to provide your latest PF passbook or balance details.\n\n3. **Verify Details:**\n   - Ensure the information provided matches your records and expectations.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Keep Your UAN Active:** Ensure that your UAN is activated and all your KYC details (like Aadhaar, PAN, and bank account) are updated.\n  \n- **Check Employer Contributions:** Regularly verify that both your and your employer's contributions are being correctly deposited into your PF account.\n\n- **Password Management:** If you forget your password, use the **\"Forgot Password\"** option on the EPF member portal or the UMANG app to reset it.\n\n- **Security:** Always keep your UAN and password confidential to protect your personal and financial information.\n\nBy following these methods, you can conveniently keep track of your PF balance and ensure that your provident fund is managed correctly.",
